        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 5:47PM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 546 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northwest of Knowles, or 12 miles southeast of Meade State
Park, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern Meade
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for southwestern
Kansas.</instruction>
